	(text_box "Using two 5V regulators to try to provide some sort of isolation between the power supply for the ESP32 and the relay coil.\n\nMaybe simpler than using an optoisolator  ... ?\n\nYes, it's not truly isolated - same +12V input and same ground, but ... it should be pretty good ... good enough for me."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 119.38 140.97 0)
		(size 125.73 12.7)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "535c3788-d3a3-4817-8d63-64e9952081d9")
	)
	(text_box "Trying to save power by using NC contact so relay coil is de-energised most of the time.\n\nWhen the router needs to be reset then we energise the coil to NO, cutting the through power.\n\nIn case of power loss, well the router will lose power too.  We want to reboot so router power can flow when relay coil is de-energised."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 173.99 49.53 0)
		(size 54.61 21.59)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d92494fa-a3c2-4f10-950f-32a3a42a1299")
	)
